# Cursor — Backend (Rust / IC canister)

Authoritative sources:

- [docs/ai/backend/structure.md](mdc:docs/ai/backend/structure.md)
- [docs/ai/backend/patterns.md](mdc:docs/ai/backend/patterns.md)
- [docs/ai/backend/testing.md](mdc:docs/ai/backend/testing.md)

## Crates

- **`backend`** ([`src/backend/`](mdc:src/backend/Cargo.toml)) — the canister
  itself. Compiles to `wasm32-unknown-unknown`. Entry point is
  [`src/backend/src/lib.rs`](mdc:src/backend/src/lib.rs) with `#[init]`,
  `#[post_upgrade]`, and `export_candid!()`.
- **`shared`** ([`src/shared/`](mdc:src/shared/Cargo.toml)) — request /
  response types, validation, utilities reused across crates and exposed in
  the Candid interface. Never put canister-only logic here.

## Module layout (`src/backend/src/`)

```
api/        Public update/query handlers, one module per area
state/      Stable state + memory IDs (StableBTreeMap, StableCell)
types/      Canister-internal types + Storable wrappers
signer/     Threshold-signature plumbing (chain-fusion signer)
bitcoin/, contacts/, exchange/, transactions/, user_profile/, token/  Domain modules
utils/      Internal helpers (housekeeping timers, …)
status/     /status endpoint
delegation.rs, benchmark.rs
lib.rs      Top-level wire-up
```

## Idioms (strict)

- **No `unwrap()` / `expect()` outside tests.** Return a typed error from
  `shared::types::result_types` or trap with a clear message via
  `ic_cdk::trap`.
- **Single state borrow.** Mutate via `state::mutate_state(|s| ...)` and
  read via `state::read_state(|s| ...)`. Don't hold a borrow across `await`.
- **`thread_local!` `STATE`** is the only state. Don't introduce parallel
  globals.
- **Stable structures only** for persisted data — `StableBTreeMap`,
  `StableCell` keyed by `MemoryId` from `state::memory`. Bumping or reusing
  a `MemoryId` is a state migration; see
  [docs/ai/backend/workflows/state-and-migrations.md](mdc:docs/ai/backend/workflows/state-and-migrations.md).
- **Disallowed macros** (clippy enforces — see
  [`clippy.toml`](mdc:clippy.toml)):
  - `std::print` / `std::println` / `std::eprint` / `std::eprintln` →
    use `ic_cdk::print` / `ic_cdk::println`.
  - `std::assert_eq` in tests → use `pretty_assertions::assert_eq`.
- **Disallowed methods:** raw `sign_with_ecdsa` / `sign_with_schnorr` —
  threshold signatures go through the chain-fusion signer canister only.
- **Workspace dependencies.** Every dependency must be declared in the root
  `Cargo.toml` workspace and referenced as `pkg.workspace = true` from each
  crate. `./scripts/lint.cargo-workspace-dependencies.sh` enforces this.
- **Wildcard imports** are warned (`#![warn(clippy::wildcard_imports)]` is
  on in `lib.rs`). Import explicit symbols.

## Public API (`backend.did` + Candid)

- The Candid file [`src/backend/backend.did`](mdc:src/backend/backend.did)
  is the source of truth for the canister interface. After changing
  `lib.rs`, regenerate via `npm run generate` (or `./scripts/did.sh`) and
  commit both the `.did` and the regenerated `src/declarations/`.
- Any change to `backend.did` is **breaking-interface** unless proven
  otherwise — see
  [docs/ai/backend/workflows/breaking-interface.md](mdc:docs/ai/backend/workflows/breaking-interface.md)
  and add `!` + `BREAKING CHANGE:` to the PR title and body when needed.

## Testing

- Integration tests live under
  [`src/backend/tests/it/`](mdc:src/backend/tests/it). Run with
  `./scripts/test.backend.sh` (downloads `pocket-ic`, BTC canister, II,
  cycles ledger, builds the canister, runs `cargo test -p backend`).
- Unit tests sit next to source as `#[cfg(test)] mod tests { … }`.
- Use `pretty_assertions::assert_eq` (clippy enforces).

## Benchmarks (`canbench-rs`)

- Suite at [`src/backend/src/benchmark.rs`](mdc:src/backend/src/benchmark.rs),
  feature-gated behind `canbench-rs`, configured by
  [`canbench.yml`](mdc:canbench.yml), results tracked in
  [`canbench_results.yml`](mdc:canbench_results.yml).
- Run `npm run benchmark` (= `canbench --persist --show-summary`).
  Commit the regenerated `canbench_results.yml` together with the change
  that caused the delta.
- **Add a bench** when you touch a hot path on a user-scaling
  `StableBTreeMap` (user_profile, contacts, custom_tokens,
  user_transactions, token_activity). Mirror an existing
  `bench_<method>` / `bench_<method>_<N>` pair.
- Lightly maintained — not gated by CI yet. See
  [docs/ai/backend/testing.md#benchmarks--canbench](mdc:docs/ai/backend/testing.md).

## Anti-patterns (reject these)

- New `unwrap()` / `expect()` in non-test code.
- New `panic!()` outside `init` / `post_upgrade` traps.
- Holding a state borrow across `.await`.
- Logging via `std::println!` (use `ic_cdk::println!`).
- Adding a dependency only inside a single crate's `Cargo.toml` without
  routing it through the workspace.
- Editing `src/declarations/**` by hand.
